1
00:00:07,400 --> 00:00:11,460
♪Just To Meet You, you fell for me♪

2
00:00:11,480 --> 00:00:15,460
♪Just to meet me, into my trap you fell♪

3
00:00:15,460 --> 00:00:19,240
♪Wanna try a breathless love?♪

4
00:00:19,240 --> 00:00:23,490
♪Every move hits the heart, close and sure♪

5
00:00:23,490 --> 00:00:27,460
♪Just To Meet You, you love my playful charm♪

6
00:00:27,460 --> 00:00:31,480
♪Just to meet me,
my romantic little schemes for you♪

7
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:35,170
♪Wanna play another brand-new game?♪

8
00:00:35,170 --> 00:00:40,360
♪Layer by layer, we close the gap♪

9
00:00:40,380 --> 00:00:47,140
=Just To Meet You=

10
00:00:47,180 --> 00:00:48,740
=Episode 23=
=Back to Where It Began=

11
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:56,960
I just couldn't wait any longer,

12
00:00:56,960 --> 00:00:58,390
so I had to do it myself.

13
00:01:00,110 --> 00:01:01,390
Jiang Niannian

14
00:01:01,790 --> 00:01:02,750
is too smart

15
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:05,040
and too soft-hearted.

16
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:08,200
Counting on her to pull this off

17
00:01:09,040 --> 00:01:10,200
was never going to work.

18
00:01:12,070 --> 00:01:12,910
Stop!

19
00:01:20,040 --> 00:01:20,880
Murong Xue.

20
00:01:20,950 --> 00:01:21,790
Stop here.

21
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:23,760
The police have surrounded the hospital.

22
00:01:25,350 --> 00:01:26,230
Why?

23
00:01:28,590 --> 00:01:31,560
I got you your first three husbands' estates.

24
00:01:32,710 --> 00:01:33,640
And even

25
00:01:34,230 --> 00:01:36,920
let you take over the Li Group with ease.

26
00:01:39,710 --> 00:01:41,280
Shouldn't you be thanking me?

27
00:01:43,680 --> 00:01:45,350
Why are you stopping my revenge?

28
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:48,560
Hatred is not an excuse to harm the innocent.

29
00:01:49,230 --> 00:01:50,280
Your mother's tragedy

30
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:52,120
shouldn't become a source of pain.

31
00:01:52,590 --> 00:01:53,430
Murong Xue,

32
00:01:53,710 --> 00:01:55,590
using innocent lives to repay your hatred,

33
00:01:55,870 --> 00:01:58,000
are you any different from them?

34
00:01:58,590 --> 00:01:59,560
Stop now.

35
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:00,480
There's still time.

36
00:02:07,070 --> 00:02:07,910
Too late.

37
00:02:09,430 --> 00:02:10,280
Once you start

38
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:12,840
some things,

39
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:15,750
you can only end one way.

40
00:02:22,470 --> 00:02:23,560
No more talking.

41
00:02:23,710 --> 00:02:24,560
Go save Ye Lang!

42
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:33,240
Ye Lang!

43
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:35,840
Ye Lang!

44
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:38,840
Ye Lang!

45
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:40,470
Ye Lang, wake up.

46
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:41,840
Ye Lang.

47
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:42,800
Wake up.

48
00:02:43,310 --> 00:02:44,150
Ye Lang.

49
00:02:44,310 --> 00:02:45,150
Ye Lang.

50
00:02:46,310 --> 00:02:47,150
Ye Lang.

51
00:02:49,150 --> 00:02:49,990
Ye Lang.

52
00:02:50,470 --> 00:02:51,560
You've gone too far.

53
00:02:57,150 --> 00:02:58,430
Don't ever do that again.

54
00:02:59,710 --> 00:03:01,120
No matter what happens,

55
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:03,560
let's never be apart, okay?

56
00:03:04,710 --> 00:03:05,550
I'm sorry.

57
00:03:06,590 --> 00:03:07,750
I made you worry.

58
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:15,520
You thought

59
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:17,310
it was all over?

60
00:03:18,910 --> 00:03:19,750
Ye Lang.

61
00:03:20,630 --> 00:03:21,520
Jiang Niannian.

62
00:03:23,190 --> 00:03:24,240
It was your hatred

63
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:26,470
that gave me endless shots at payback.

64
00:03:29,310 --> 00:03:30,360
I will always

65
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:35,080
come out on top.

66
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:37,920
Ye Lang.

67
00:03:39,150 --> 00:03:40,030
What does she mean?

68
00:03:40,710 --> 00:03:41,550
Is she like you?

69
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:43,080
Reborn with her memories?

70
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:45,000
We won't repeat this, right?

71
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:48,310
As long as we let go of the past,

72
00:03:49,030 --> 00:03:51,080
the cycle of pain won't repeat.

73
00:03:52,590 --> 00:03:53,430
Niannian.

74
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:55,120
Don't worry.

75
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:59,240
It's all over now.

76
00:04:08,750 --> 00:04:09,680
What a pity.

77
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:10,990
Looks like

78
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:12,680
I won't get to dissect you.

79
00:04:14,430 --> 00:04:15,840
At a time like this,

80
00:04:16,950 --> 00:04:18,360
you're still joking?

81
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:19,760
Alright.

82
00:04:20,190 --> 00:04:21,190
Come on, Ms. Murong.

83
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:22,480
Let's have a talk.

84
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:25,320
Let's go.

85
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:26,760
Ye Lang.

86
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:30,840
Ye Lang.

87
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:33,200
Ye Lang!

88
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:36,520
Ye Lang.

89
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:39,400
Niannian.

90
00:04:40,630 --> 00:04:41,470
Ye Lang.

91
00:04:43,750 --> 00:04:45,000
When I get well,

92
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:49,190
let's go back to the fishing village.

93
00:04:49,950 --> 00:04:50,790
Okay.

94
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:53,520
I promise you.

95
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:55,560
As long as

96
00:04:56,830 --> 00:04:57,720
we let go of hatred,

97
00:04:59,160 --> 00:05:01,480
the cycle of pain won't repeat.

98
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:04,520
Niannian.

99
00:05:05,830 --> 00:05:07,120
I promised you

100
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:10,480
I'd give you a happy life.

101
00:05:11,930 --> 00:05:15,230
♪Letting go of all calculations♪

102
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:16,200
We are

103
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:17,590
going to have a

104
00:05:18,390 --> 00:05:19,870
wonderful future.

105
00:05:20,870 --> 00:05:21,710
Ye Lang!

106
00:05:22,870 --> 00:05:23,710
Ye Lang!

107
00:05:24,950 --> 00:05:25,790
Ye Lang!

108
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:28,750
Ye Lang!

109
00:05:30,070 --> 00:05:31,040
Ye Lang!

110
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:35,490
♪Yet somehow we meet again♪

111
00:05:35,510 --> 00:05:36,350
Ye Lang.

112
00:05:36,820 --> 00:05:39,800
♪And somehow it's still you♪

113
00:05:39,830 --> 00:05:42,190
♪Don't let me go♪

114
00:05:42,570 --> 00:05:45,750
♪Let me look into your eyes♪

115
00:05:46,070 --> 00:05:49,220
♪Help me believe again♪

116
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:56,860
♪Shape unknown roads into your journey♪

117
00:05:56,860 --> 00:05:59,460
(Previous Life)

118
00:05:59,540 --> 00:06:17,580
(Previous Life)

119
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,040
The wedding's about to start.

120
00:06:19,070 --> 00:06:19,950
Why're you here now?

121
00:06:20,630 --> 00:06:22,480
I haven't seen you for 24 hours.

122
00:06:23,510 --> 00:06:24,630
If I didn't see you soon,

123
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:26,310
I felt like I'd die.

124
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:31,230
Niannian.

125
00:06:32,190 --> 00:06:33,600
This feels like a dream.

126
00:06:34,630 --> 00:06:36,950
From now on,
let's never be apart again.

127
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:43,520
Niannian.

128
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,080
It turns out

129
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,190
that when people are truly happy,

130
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:49,800
they can actually feel pain.

131
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:52,800
If you've something
to do with Xiaodi's death,

132
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:55,950
go to hell then.

133
00:06:56,390 --> 00:06:57,230
Niannian.

134
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:30,320
Why?

135
00:07:31,870 --> 00:07:33,070
Why did you do that?

136
00:07:35,430 --> 00:07:37,040
I saw you couldn't do it yourself,

137
00:07:37,310 --> 00:07:38,310
so I helped you.

138
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:43,360
But I didn't want him dead.

139
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:45,630
I just wanted to ask him

140
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:48,600
if Xiaodi's death was tied to him.

141
00:07:51,190 --> 00:07:52,030
Well,

142
00:07:53,310 --> 00:07:54,430
the answer is right here.

143
00:08:24,070 --> 00:08:25,240
Like what you see?

144
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:42,670
I killed Ye Lang for you.

145
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:44,720
How are you going to reward me?

146
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:45,560
Xue.

147
00:08:48,910 --> 00:08:51,200
I gave you such a perfect new heart.

148
00:08:52,630 --> 00:08:54,080
So how should you reward me?

149
00:08:58,510 --> 00:08:59,350
Xue.

150
00:09:00,150 --> 00:09:01,270
I did everything

151
00:09:01,750 --> 00:09:02,630
you told me to do.

152
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:10,360
Thanks for playing your part.

153
00:09:11,750 --> 00:09:13,000
The truth is, your heart

154
00:09:14,330 --> 00:09:15,920
had no problem.

155
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:19,520
The one I replaced was the bad one.

156
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,040
A bad heart...

157
00:09:34,630 --> 00:09:35,470
The heart...

158
00:09:36,630 --> 00:09:37,510
Something's wrong

159
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:38,750
with my heart.

160
00:09:42,790 --> 00:09:43,750
Xue.

161
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,200
Xue.

162
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:46,280
Help me.

163
00:09:46,630 --> 00:09:47,470
Help me.

164
00:09:49,390 --> 00:09:50,230
Xue.

165
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:51,960
Xue, help me.

166
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:54,270
Don't hurt her!

167
00:09:55,790 --> 00:09:57,240
Why did you take Xiaodi's heart?

168
00:09:58,270 --> 00:09:59,360
He's only fifteen.

169
00:10:00,790 --> 00:10:01,910
He's innocent!

170
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:03,960
Back then,

171
00:10:04,910 --> 00:10:05,750
when Li Hong

172
00:10:06,550 --> 00:10:07,910
and Ye Lang's grandfather

173
00:10:08,910 --> 00:10:10,720
took my mother's heart,

174
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:14,080
did they ever think she was innocent?

175
00:10:28,870 --> 00:10:30,440
You were a victim too.

176
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:32,560
Why?

177
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:35,270
Why continue this evil?

178
00:10:37,390 --> 00:10:39,750
Because this world was never fair.

179
00:10:41,030 --> 00:10:42,030
For some to live,

180
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:44,870
others must die.

181
00:10:45,900 --> 00:10:46,820
If you don't hurt them,

182
00:10:46,820 --> 00:10:48,160
they'll come after you!

183
00:10:49,030 --> 00:10:50,240
Better to be the hunter

184
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:52,330
than the one getting cut down.

185
00:11:02,910 --> 00:11:03,750
Doctor!

186
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:04,910
Doctor!

187
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:06,480
Please save Ye Lang first!

188
00:11:33,470 --> 00:11:40,030
♪Stitched-up lips
tear open a blood-red dusk♪

189
00:11:41,870 --> 00:11:48,070
♪You return reborn,
seeing through all my cracks♪

190
00:11:48,630 --> 00:11:55,630
♪This tenderness, a trap or a gift?♪

191
00:11:56,350 --> 00:11:58,830
♪Still, I'd wager my next life on it♪

192
00:11:58,830 --> 00:12:03,830
♪Just for a moment to recognize you again♪

193
00:12:03,830 --> 00:12:08,070
♪You are the blazing light in my despair♪

194
00:12:08,590 --> 00:12:12,510
♪Lighting the edges of my frozen wings♪

195
00:12:12,550 --> 00:12:16,350
♪I burn myself,
leaping into an illusion of fire♪

196
00:12:16,350 --> 00:12:22,110
♪Breaking free
from dead vines in the ashes♪

197
00:12:22,110 --> 00:12:26,430
♪You are the brightest star in the night♪

198
00:12:26,470 --> 00:12:30,270
♪Awakening my dormant fate♪

199
00:12:30,270 --> 00:12:34,790
♪Freeing me from this half-life prison♪

200
00:12:34,790 --> 00:12:39,630
♪As the bells shatter the past♪

201
00:12:40,030 --> 00:12:46,590
♪Life finds its way again♪
